# Keep Cursor Rules Up to Date

After making any of the following kinds of changes, update the relevant rule file in `.cursor/rules/`:

| Change type | Rule file to update |
|-------------|-------------------|
| New data type or changed field shape | `core-data-types.mdc` |
| New state variable or changed update pattern in `FlowChart.tsx` | `state-architecture.mdc` |
| New tree mutation function or changed slice logic | `tree-and-slices.mdc` |
| New machine option source or changed filtering logic | `machine-options.mdc` |
| Changed flow rate computation or storage balance | `flow-rates-and-storage.mdc` |
| New persistence key, migration, or storage API | `persistence.mdc` |
| New top-level directory, framework change, or major new feature | `project-overview.mdc` |

Rules live in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`. Keep each rule under ~50 lines — split into a new file if a topic grows large.
